text: Chicken paprikash is a Hungarian stew made with chicken meat that is seasoned with paprika. The food was brought to the United States by Hungarian Jewish immigrants. ==Ingredients== Chicken paprikash is made by cooking chicken pieces in a small amount of butter. Then, the chicken is added to a broth made out of water, paprika, garlic and other spices. Some people add tomato to the chicken paprikash. ==References== Category:Chicken as food Category:Hungarian food
title: Chicken paprikash
